# RetailS Pose-BiLSTM (One-Class Anomaly Detection)

This project trains a **BiLSTM-based one-class anomaly model** for shoplifting detection using pre-extracted RetailS pose JSON files.

## What This Pipeline Does

1. Loads pose JSON files directly (no YOLO/ByteTrack/HRNet rerun).
2. Groups by person ID and frame ID into temporal sequences.
3. Builds fixed-length windows (default: 30, stride: 5).
4. Trains a BiLSTM autoencoder on RetailS train split (normal-only).
5. Computes frame-level anomaly scores on staged and real-world test splits.
6. Evaluates with HPRS (primary), plus PR-AUC, ROC-AUC, F1, precision, recall, specificity.

## Feature Engineering

Per frame, the model uses:

- Normalized joint positions (COCO17):
  - center at hip center (left/right hip mean)
  - scale by torso length (shoulder center to hip center), fallback to bbox diagonal
- Temporal dynamics:
  - velocity (first difference)
  - acceleration (second difference)
- Relational features:
  - left wrist to left hip distance
  - right wrist to right hip distance
  - left/right wrist to torso center distances
  - wrist-to-wrist distance
- Joint confidence features:
  - confidence for each of 17 joints

## Dataset Assumptions

Default config expects:

- `/home/damelikassym/RetailS/RetailS/RetailS_train/pose/train/*.json`
- `/home/damelikassym/RetailS/RetailS/RetailS_test_staged/pose/test/*.json`
- `/home/damelikassym/RetailS/RetailS/RetailS_test_staged/gt/test_frame_mask/*.npy`
- `/home/damelikassym/RetailS/RetailS/RetailS_test_realworld/pose/test/*.json`
- `/home/damelikassym/RetailS/RetailS/RetailS_test_realworld/gt/test_frame_mask/*.npy`

Update `configs/default.yaml` if your dataset path changes.

## One-Command End-to-End Run

```bash
cd /home/damelikassym/retails-bilstm
bash scripts/run_full_pipeline.sh
```

This creates:

- `runs/full_*/train/train_summary.json`
- `runs/full_*/train/best_model.pt`
- `runs/full_*/eval/eval_report.json`

## Manual Commands

```bash
cd /home/damelikassym/retails-bilstm
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
python -m pip install --upgrade torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m pip install -e .

# Train only
retails-bilstm train --config configs/default.yaml --output-dir runs/train_exp

# Evaluate only
retails-bilstm evaluate --config configs/default.yaml --checkpoint runs/train_exp/best_model.pt --output-dir runs/eval_exp
```

## Notes on Metrics

- **Primary model-selection metric**: HPRS (harmonic mean of precision, recall, specificity).
- Two operating points are reported:
  - Unsupervised threshold (from train reconstruction-error quantile).
  - Tuned threshold (best HPRS on staged set), then transferred to real-world set.

## GPU + CUDA

- Pipeline supports GPU training with mixed precision (AMP).
- Batch size can be auto-selected to better utilize a 24GB GPU.
- Default script installs CUDA-enabled PyTorch wheels (`cu128`) to avoid local CUDA toolkit conflicts.
